Transactions on the equities sector of the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE), reopened upbeat yesterday, as more high capital stocks joined the league of gainers, resulting in a further rise in market capitalisation by N98 billion.
 
At the close of trading yesterday, the All-Share Index (ASI), rose 188.50 absolute points, or 0.72 per cent to close at 26,507.84 points. Similarly, the overall market capitalisation gained N98 billion to close at N13.853 trillion.  Analysts at Afrinvest Limited, said: “We anticipate a sustained bullish momentum in the next trading session.”  FCMB Group traded 27.850 million shares at N58.392 million, and Guaranty Trust Bank transacted 14.657 million shares worth N396.215 million. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .